data.title: Catalogue of Works
data.meta_description: Woolf Projects - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document discusses Jonathan Woolf, an architect and founder of Woolf Architects. It summarizes Robert Maxwell's changing views on modern architecture and praise for Woolf's narrative approach. It then describes a house designed by Woolf called Brick Leaf House, praising its restrained materiality and spatial sequences that provide calmness while connecting to the landscape. It concludes by discussing Woolf's skilled adaptations and renovations of older buildings that breathe new life into them in a sophisticated way.
